#    "likle" Kohl)
#
#  Maintained by Pablo Delgado Krämer (pablode/guc).  149 GH stars.
#  guc converts glTF 2.0 / GLB 3D model files to Pixar Universal Scene
#  Description (USD) format with MaterialX support — used in 3D content
#  pipelines for Pixar/Apple workflows, USD-based asset stores, and
#  USD-supporting renderers (Hydra, Storm, RenderMan, Karma, Cycles).
#  Sister tools: gltfjsx (R3F JSX converter, IN CORPUS via _gltfjsx,
#  R393), gltf-pipeline (CesiumJS, IN CORPUS), gltf-transform
#  (donmccurdy, IN CORPUS), Pixar USD tools `usdcat`/`usdedit`/
#  `usdview` (IN CORPUS via _usd-related), MaterialX (Lucasfilm/ILM
#  shading networks).
#
#  CLI library taxonomy update: 3rd C CLI library — Pascal Kohl's
#  **cargs** (likle/cargs).  C ecosystem now has 3 documented CLI
#  libraries (R272 POSIX getopt + R382 GNU argp + R394 cargs).
#
#  cargs (likle/cargs) is Pascal Kohl's modern lightweight cross-
#  platform C CLI argument parser — described as "a lightweight
#  cross-platform getopt alternative that is tested on Linux,
#  Windows, MacOS, FreeBSD, OpenBSD and NetBSD".  229 GH stars.
#  Distinct from R272 C POSIX getopt (Unix-only, char-by-char
#  iteration, no Windows portability) and R382 GNU argp (glibc-only,
#  parser-callback model, GNU/Linux-specific) by being CROSS-PLATFORM
#  with consistent API across Unix and Windows.  Used by Microsoft
#  voxelpic (point cloud to voxel image library), Pablo Delgado
#  Krämer's guc (glTF to USD converter, 149 stars), HydraUSB3
#  toolchain (WCH CH56X chip ISP programmer), Fennix hobby OS,
#  AirDeeEx/lvterm terminal, cimplecrypt, Black-Mesas/outfittable,
#  MauroGuar/redit, mk-nice CPU scheduler, scimusmn/tsck-microbots,
#  enderice2/Fennix, I3uckwheat/git-note, kiishor/xml_code_generator,
#  Jason23347/ustb-cli-c, djohansson/speedo, and many cross-platform
#  C CLI tools that want POSIX-getopt-like semantics without the
#  portability headaches.
